description:
Given an integer array nums, return the maximum result of nums[i] XOR nums[j], where 0 <= i <= j < n.
### Example 1



### Input

```CPP
nums = [3,10,5,25,2,8]
```

### Output

```CPP
28
```

### Example 2



### Input

```CPP
nums = [14,70,53,83,49,91,36,80,92,51,66,70]
```

### Output

```CPP
127
```

### Constraints:

- 1 <= nums.length <= 2 * 10^5
- 0 <= nums[i] <= 2^31 - 1
title: Maximum Xor
